.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. William De Venables was born about 1204, in Kinderton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William De VENABLES in 1225, in Kinderton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters."},"et":{"Abt 1204–":"umbes 1204–Surnud","1201–Male":"1201–Surnud","1224–1273":"1224–1273","1230–1288":"1230–1288","1204–Female":"1204–Surnud","1204":"1204","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1288":"1288","about 1224":"umbes 1224","Abt 1204":"umbes 1204","1230":"1230","1273":"1273","Kinderton,Middlewich,Cheshire,England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wincham, Cheshire, England":"Wincham, Cheshire, England","Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1204–":"noin 1204–Kuollut","1201–Male":"1201–Kuollut","1224–1273":"1224–1273","1230–1288":"1230–1288","1204–Female":"1204–Kuollut","1204":"1204","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1201":"1201","1288":"1288","about 1224":"noin 1224","Abt 1204":"noin 1204","1230":"1230","1273":"1273","Kinderton,Middlewich,Cheshire,England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wincham, Cheshire, England":"Wincham, Cheshire, England","Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1204–":"environ 1204–Décédée","1201–Male":"1201–Décédé","1224–1273":"1224–1273","1230–1